1
00:00:42,657 --> 00:00:45,300
My name is Andre. Andre Moussa.

2
00:00:45,400 --> 00:00:48,800
28 years old. Single. U.S. citizen.

3
00:00:49,000 --> 00:00:53,102
Paris is a wonderful city, although I don't really have the time to enjoy it.
Too much work...

4
00:00:53,500 --> 00:00:56,800
I also do business in Argentina, Chile... a bit in China.

5
00:00:56,801 --> 00:01:01,801
Almost nothing in the U.S., actually.
Just my penthouse in N.Y.C., right above Central Park.

6
00:01:01,802 --> 00:01:04,802
Let's focus on Paris...
I've made many friends here.

7
00:01:04,803 --> 00:01:09,400
I used to think the French would be angry about the Iraq war,
and this silly disagreement between our countries.

8
00:01:09,401 --> 00:01:11,500
But it's not the case.

9
00:01:11,501 --> 00:01:14,805
Maybe it's thanks to my behaviour.
I'm nice, generous...

10
00:01:15,806 --> 00:01:19,100
I'm not too bad in bed.
Things are going well for me.

11
00:01:19,101 --> 00:01:23,101
I think I can tell sincerely that I am a nice guy.

12
00:01:23,102 --> 00:01:29,102
Here you go. That's all I can tell you about me.
Who I would like to be. ... would dream to be.

13
00:01:29,500 --> 00:01:30,500
Because I'm lying.

14
00:01:31,504 --> 00:01:32,104
To myself.

15
00:01:32,800 --> 00:01:34,000
To everyone.

16
00:01:34,500 --> 00:01:35,500
All day.

17
00:01:39,050 --> 00:01:42,801
You really are an American piece of crap.
Do you believe we're going to believe that story?

18
00:01:42,802 --> 00:01:45,802
I'm not American. I told you...
I won my green card at the lottery.

19
00:01:45,803 --> 00:01:48,000
They do that every year.
I'm from Morocco.

20
00:01:48,001 --> 00:01:50,001
I don't like Arabs either!

21
00:01:52,002 --> 00:01:54,002
Stop punching, damnit!

22
00:01:54,003 --> 00:01:57,003
It's a misunderstanding.
I didn't have the time to explain.

23
00:01:57,004 --> 00:01:58,254
Okay. You have 10 seconds.

24
00:02:09,000 --> 00:02:09,702
Here you go.

25
00:02:10,000 --> 00:02:11,703
If it wasn't for that, I would have repaid you a long time ago.

26
00:02:11,704 --> 00:02:14,000
And you don't have a credit card?

27
00:02:14,001 --> 00:02:16,700
If I had a card, I would have gotten cash anywhere.
There's one of those banks with the squirrel, right here.

28
00:02:16,701 --> 00:02:17,400
Shut up!

29
00:02:17,401 --> 00:02:20,401
Shut your mouth! When you open it, it pisses me off even more.

30
00:02:20,402 --> 00:02:22,000
No, you haven't understood.

31
00:02:22,001 --> 00:02:25,300
Don't even say 'okay'.
Shut your mouth 100%.

32
00:02:25,301 --> 00:02:26,601
You understand '100%' ?

33
00:02:26,602 --> 00:02:30,150
Don't say a single word.
Breathe. That's all.

34
00:02:35,151 --> 00:02:37,000
Here you go. Good.

35
00:02:39,000 --> 00:02:40,500
That must be tough.

36
00:02:40,501 --> 00:02:42,501
For a fucking American like you...
Shutting up.

37
00:02:44,502 --> 00:02:46,502
You who always want to teach lessons to the world.

38
00:02:47,503 --> 00:02:52,000
No comment. Just shut up.
And quietly listen to what I have to say.

39
00:02:52,001 --> 00:02:55,001
Mamou... Do you remember Monsieur Mamou?

40
00:03:00,500 --> 00:03:02,500
You owe money to Monsieur Mamou.

41
00:03:02,501 --> 00:03:06,450
40,000 Euros !
Not shitty Dollars... Euros!

42
00:03:07,650 --> 00:03:12,000
And if you haven't returned them by tonight.
I will find you, and break your fingers.

43
00:03:12,001 --> 00:03:14,151
And if it's not enough, I'll break your arms.

44
00:03:14,152 --> 00:03:15,152
And your legs.

45
00:03:15,153 --> 00:03:16,153
And your head.

46
00:03:19,000 --> 00:03:20,000
I know that song... I like it.

47
00:03:20,001 --> 00:03:23,980
You have until tonight.
And tonight ends at midnight.

48
00:03:23,981 --> 00:03:27,500
After that, it's tomorrow.
And tomorrow, you'll be dead!

49
00:03:29,500 --> 00:03:31,000
See you later.

50
00:03:38,001 --> 00:03:40,500
Suddenly, two things had become very clear to me.

51
00:03:40,501 --> 00:03:45,150
I really had to do something.
And I definitely hated Paris.

52
00:03:45,151 --> 00:03:46,151
Monsieur Frank!

53
00:03:49,201 --> 00:03:51,900
Please... Monsieur Frank.

54
00:04:03,000 --> 00:04:04,860
I don't really understand, Andre.

55
00:04:04,861 --> 00:04:09,900
I welcome you in my home, as a friend. Introduce you to people.
Lend you money when you're in need.

56
00:04:09,901 --> 00:04:10,901
And what do I get in return?

57
00:04:10,902 --> 00:04:11,902
I can explain!

58
00:04:11,903 --> 00:04:16,000
Not a word. Not a phonecall.
And now you make me climb the fucking Eiffel tower to find you...

59
00:04:16,001 --> 00:04:17,500
Do you really think I have the time to be a tourist?

60
00:04:17,501 --> 00:04:21,500
No, of course you're not a tourist, Monsieur Frank.
I can explain... please!

61
00:04:23,000 --> 00:04:24,100
Go ahead, I'm listening.

62
00:04:24,101 --> 00:04:27,224
Can you ask this gentleman to bring me back on the ground?
It would me more convenient...

63
00:04:27,225 --> 00:04:29,100
I hear you just fine from here.
Hurry up, I'm running late.

64
00:04:29,101 --> 00:04:33,000
I've lost my identification, my passport and all my credit cards.
I went to the American Express offices.

65
00:04:33,001 --> 00:04:34,001
Let go of him.

66
00:04:34,002 --> 00:04:36,002
No, Frank! Please!
Don't let go!

67
00:04:38,500 --> 00:04:41,003
Monsieur Frank!
Please!

68
00:04:43,004 --> 00:04:44,004
Something to add?

69
00:04:44,005 --> 00:04:46,005
Tonight.
I'm paying tonight.

70
00:04:46,006 --> 00:04:47,600
On my mother's head! I'm paying tonight.

71
00:04:47,601 --> 00:04:48,900
Why should I care?
I don't know your mother.

72
00:04:48,901 --> 00:04:50,450
I'm paying everything tonight.
On the whoever's head you want.

73
00:04:50,451 --> 00:04:53,000
And how do you intend to do that?
You're broke, and indebted to everybody in Paris.

74
00:04:53,001 --> 00:04:54,100
I don't know. I don't know.

75
00:04:55,000 --> 00:04:57,200
But I'm having a hard time thinking
I'm my current position.

76
00:04:58,500 --> 00:05:00,200
You're aware that I have men in every train station?

77
00:05:00,201 --> 00:05:01,201
I know, Monsieur Frank.

78
00:05:02,800 --> 00:05:04,000
So, don't try to run.

79
00:05:04,001 --> 00:05:06,700
No.
That would be a very bad idea.

80
00:05:08,000 --> 00:05:09,200
I give you until midnight.

81
00:05:09,901 --> 00:05:11,100
Thank you, Monsieur Frank.

82
00:05:47,000 --> 00:05:49,001
You have no idea how glad I am to see you, Monsieur.

83
00:05:49,002 --> 00:05:51,400
Good morning, sir.
Can I see your papers, please?

84
00:05:51,405 --> 00:05:53,600
No, but don't worry, I'm American.

85
00:05:55,000 --> 00:05:56,650
Did you block your credit cards?

86
00:05:56,651 --> 00:05:59,000
Yes. All of them.
And now I can't get cash anymore.

87
00:05:59,001 --> 00:06:01,450
It makes things rather difficult.
Life is so expensive in Paris...

88
00:06:01,451 --> 00:06:02,451
I know...

89
00:06:02,452 --> 00:06:05,000
But American Express can make you a new card in 24 hours,
can't they?

90
00:06:05,001 --> 00:06:07,690
Yes, but for that I need to prove my identity.

91
00:06:07,691 --> 00:06:10,000
And since I don't have my papers anymore,
I can't prove my identity.

92
00:06:10,001 --> 00:06:11,500
Ah, yes...
It's a vicious circle.

93
00:06:11,501 --> 00:06:15,200
On top of that, it's Saturday.
All my friends have either gone to the country or on holidays.

94
00:06:15,201 --> 00:06:17,100
Baldwin alley, it's in Manhattan?

95
00:06:17,101 --> 00:06:19,750
No. Brooklyn.
Number 720. 5th floor.

96
00:06:19,751 --> 00:06:20,751
You want the phone number?

97
00:06:20,752 --> 00:06:22,500
No, it's okay.
I have it already.

98
00:06:23,500 --> 00:06:26,400
Really?
You have this kind of data in the computer?

99
00:06:26,401 --> 00:06:29,000
Yes. I also have your three condemnations.

100
00:06:29,500 --> 00:06:30,501
Really?

101
00:06:31,502 --> 00:06:34,800
Then it must have told you that it's ancient history.
I was young...

102
00:06:35,250 --> 00:06:36,500
The last one was three months ago.

103
00:06:36,501 --> 00:06:39,300
Ah...
You have this one too?

104
00:06:41,700 --> 00:06:42,800
That computer is powerful.

105
00:06:44,500 --> 00:06:46,300
Did it tell you it was a misunderstanding?

106
00:06:47,000 --> 00:06:48,700
In the report, they call it a con job.

107
00:06:48,701 --> 00:06:50,300
And you almost got three months for it.

108
00:06:50,301 --> 00:06:51,900
Yes. It's true.

109
00:06:51,901 --> 00:06:53,901
And I intend to appeal when I return.

110
00:06:53,902 --> 00:06:56,450
Monsieur Moussa, there is not much we can do for you.

111
00:06:56,451 --> 00:07:02,000
I suggest you go to the nearest police station. And declare the theft.
They will give you temporary papers.

112
00:07:05,750 --> 00:07:07,220
Listen, sir...

113
00:07:08,000 --> 00:07:09,200
I am an American citizen.

114
00:07:09,201 --> 00:07:13,700
I have rights. Written in a constitution.
For which my great-grandparents have fought their entire lives.

115
00:07:14,500 --> 00:07:17,600
I think I deserve my country's support.
Especially in such a desperate situation.

116
00:07:17,601 --> 00:07:19,200
Monsieur Moussa, your grandparents lived in Algery.

117
00:07:19,201 --> 00:07:21,000
So, maybe they fought for independance...

118
00:07:21,000 --> 00:07:22,400
But certainly not the U.S. independance.

119
00:07:22,401 --> 00:07:26,400
Keep in mind that the green card you won at the lottery
requires that you obey some rules.

120
00:07:26,401 --> 00:07:29,800
Rules written at the back of the document
that you obviously did not bother reading.

121
00:07:29,801 --> 00:07:35,740
It is clearly written that the American administration
can cancel your visa in case of severe or repeated offense.

122
00:07:35,741 --> 00:07:38,800
And in your case, you ostensibly combine both criteria.

123
00:07:38,801 --> 00:07:41,600
Now, let me give you a more personal piece of advice.

124
00:07:41,601 --> 00:07:45,051
I think that the only person that can do anything for you is... yourself.

125
00:07:45,052 --> 00:07:49,750
Please exit the building quietly.
Or I am going to call the marines in charge of security.

126
00:08:39,990 --> 00:08:41,500
Hey, Andre!
Andre!

127
00:08:42,700 --> 00:08:44,501
You've got my money, Andre?

128
00:08:44,502 --> 00:08:47,000
Hey, Andre, come here!
You fucker!

129
00:09:17,690 --> 00:09:18,300
Hi!

130
00:09:18,500 --> 00:09:20,100
What are you here for?

131
00:09:20,501 --> 00:09:24,000
Well, err...
I was thinking that... err...

132
00:09:24,001 --> 00:09:26,901
I was intending to...

133
00:09:35,000 --> 00:09:36,500
I can't take it anymore.

134
00:09:36,501 --> 00:09:38,500
I'm at the end of the rope.

135
00:09:39,300 --> 00:09:41,850
What's wrong, little fellow?

136
00:09:42,100 --> 00:09:46,000
I fucked up.
I have borrowed lots of money.

137
00:09:46,001 --> 00:09:48,500
And my calculations were slightly wrong.

138
00:09:49,300 --> 00:09:51,000
Now I can't return anything to these guys.

139
00:09:51,001 --> 00:09:52,800
And if I don't do it
they're going to shoot me.

140
00:09:54,450 --> 00:09:57,250
And you want to report them?

141
00:09:57,251 --> 00:10:02,000
Nah... reporting them...
If I do that they're going to shoot me even more.

142
00:10:03,500 --> 00:10:05,550
What can I do for you, then?

143
00:10:08,800 --> 00:10:13,150
I was thinking that... you...

144
00:10:15,450 --> 00:10:18,380
Maybe you could put me in jail for a few days...
Until I figure things out.

145
00:10:18,930 --> 00:10:22,235
That's a joke for TV? Is that it?

146
00:10:24,500 --> 00:10:26,500
No, it's not for TV.

147
00:10:27,900 --> 00:10:30,500
Can't you see I'm about to crack?
And you tell me about TV jokes!

148
00:10:30,801 --> 00:10:31,501
I'm asking you to throw me in jail!

149
00:10:31,502 --> 00:10:33,850
An Arab without any ID papers.
That shouldn't be a problem!

150
00:10:35,120 --> 00:10:36,200
What 'uh...' ?

151
00:10:40,500 --> 00:10:42,300
You bastards!

152
00:10:44,600 --> 00:10:46,400
Cowards!

153
00:10:48,000 --> 00:10:49,250
What kind of police is that?

154
00:11:17,000 --> 00:11:18,600
You only start reacting now, uh?

155
00:11:19,900 --> 00:11:21,200
Well... it's too late!

156
00:11:23,201 --> 00:11:24,250
I'm going to kill myself!

157
00:11:25,800 --> 00:11:27,400
And it's your fault.

158
00:11:41,000 --> 00:11:43,150
Nobody cares about me, is that it?

159
00:11:48,900 --> 00:11:49,999
I'm going to do it.

160
00:11:54,200 --> 00:11:55,500
Is that what you want?

161
00:11:57,200 --> 00:11:58,800
Why are you giving up on me?

162
00:12:03,000 --> 00:12:05,800
Why don't you ever answer my questions?

163
00:12:15,700 --> 00:12:17,000
What are you doing here?

164
00:12:18,400 --> 00:12:21,250
Well... the same as you.

165
00:12:21,251 --> 00:12:23,150
Meaning?

166
00:12:36,500 --> 00:12:37,800
Don't worry!

167
00:12:38,950 --> 00:12:40,500
I'm coming.
I'm here.

168
00:12:40,501 --> 00:12:42,150
Don't worry.
I'm here.

169
00:12:58,050 --> 00:13:00,600
What the hell was that all about?

170
00:13:02,100 --> 00:13:05,400
I can't even kill myself in peace.
Even there, someone has to annoy me.

171
00:13:05,650 --> 00:13:08,750
Don't I deserve a minute alone?
So that I can leave with dignity?

172
00:13:08,751 --> 00:13:10,800
You... what did you come here for?
It's Sunday morning!

173
00:13:10,801 --> 00:13:12,400
Couldn't you stay in bed, like everybody?

174
00:13:12,401 --> 00:13:13,431
I couldn't sleep.

175
00:13:13,432 --> 00:13:16,765
Then you should have chosen another bridge.
We have plenty of them in this fucking city!

176
00:13:16,766 --> 00:13:18,700
Didn't you see that one was occupied?

177
00:13:19,000 --> 00:13:21,200
We had the same idea.
Isn't that funny?

178
00:13:21,201 --> 00:13:23,700
Funny, yeah...
Hysterical.

179
00:13:24,350 --> 00:13:26,450
Can you tell me why
you want to jump off that bridge so badly?

180
00:13:26,451 --> 00:13:28,400
Probably because I have the same problems as you.

181
00:13:28,401 --> 00:13:29,401
I don't think so...

182
00:13:29,402 --> 00:13:30,700
Why?

183
00:13:31,500 --> 00:13:34,600
Because my problem is that I feel stupid,
ugly, and totally useless.

184
00:13:34,601 --> 00:13:36,750
And I don't think you have this kind of problem.

185
00:13:36,751 --> 00:13:40,150
It's exactly the same :
I'm stupid and ugly

186
00:13:40,151 --> 00:13:41,350
...on the inside.

187
00:13:43,150 --> 00:13:45,150
At least you can hide it, with your looks.

188
00:13:45,151 --> 00:13:47,000
I have nothing to hide.

189
00:13:48,000 --> 00:13:49,250
I can see that, yeah...

190
00:13:51,250 --> 00:13:54,350
Can you tell me, why a girl like you can feel so bad?

191
00:13:55,001 --> 00:13:57,000
You're young.
You're beautiful.

192
00:13:55,352 --> 00:13:59,450
The world could be at your feet.
You could ask for anything.

193
00:13:59,451 --> 00:14:01,000
So? What do I want?

194
00:14:01,001 --> 00:14:02,800
I don't know.
I'm not a psychic.

195
00:14:04,450 --> 00:14:06,450
To be rich, I guess.
Like everybody.

196
00:14:07,650 --> 00:14:09,700
To spend your money around the world.
To be attractive...

197
00:14:09,701 --> 00:14:12,000
To buy dresses, furs...

198
00:14:12,001 --> 00:14:13,750
That's what makes women happy,
if I understand correctly.

199
00:14:13,751 --> 00:14:15,800
And you?
What would make you happy?

200
00:14:15,801 --> 00:14:18,650
To be left alone, at peace...
To breathe. Here's what I need.

201
00:14:18,651 --> 00:14:21,449
I need time to figure things out.
Can't you see what I look like?

202
00:14:21,450 --> 00:14:24,350
What matters is on the inside,
no on the outside.

203
00:14:24,950 --> 00:14:27,250
Easy for you...
Don't you see how good you look?

204
00:14:27,251 --> 00:14:30,150
Women think they're the ones to talk...
Who would be dead if it wasn't for me?

205
00:14:30,151 --> 00:14:32,950
And who would be dead if he didn't
have someone to save?

206
00:14:33,000 --> 00:14:34,950
Don't you have a smoke?

207
00:14:36,400 --> 00:14:40,000
Listen... I'm not in the mood for psychological games.
Especially on a Sunday morning.

208
00:14:40,002 --> 00:14:43,500
Yeah, you're right.
What are we doing now?

209
00:14:49,850 --> 00:14:50,900
Why 'what are we doing' ?

210
00:14:50,901 --> 00:14:54,150
You saved my life.
I suppose you intend to do something with it.

211
00:14:54,151 --> 00:14:58,000
No. I didn't think.
I jumped by chance.

212
00:14:58,001 --> 00:15:00,130
People should not be left to die.
It's not good.

213
00:15:00,131 --> 00:15:02,700
I agree.
So... what do we do now?

214
00:15:02,701 --> 00:15:05,000
Nothing! Just leave me alone.

215
00:15:05,001 --> 00:15:07,500
Damn, men...
You really are all the same.

216
00:15:07,501 --> 00:15:10,400
You act without thinking,
and then you throw us away.

217
00:15:10,401 --> 00:15:13,700
That's enough.
I'm not in the mood for an argument either.

218
00:15:13,701 --> 00:15:15,400
Bye.

219
00:15:29,000 --> 00:15:30,500
What's your first name?

220
00:15:31,400 --> 00:15:32,900
Angela.

221
00:15:33,000 --> 00:15:35,750
Listen, Angela.
If I leave you like that, will you try it again?

222
00:15:35,751 --> 00:15:36,450
Try what?

223
00:15:36,451 --> 00:15:37,900
Jumping off bridges, obviously!

224
00:15:37,901 --> 00:15:39,001
It's likely...

225
00:15:39,450 --> 00:15:40,650
Can't you try changing your mind?

226
00:15:40,651 --> 00:15:42,000
Why?

227
00:15:42,001 --> 00:15:44,750
What kind if question is that?

228
00:15:45,800 --> 00:15:48,100
Because you...

229
00:15:48,101 --> 00:15:49,550
Because you're beautiful.

230
00:15:49,551 --> 00:15:51,800
And losing a pretty girl like you
would be a waste.

231
00:15:53,300 --> 00:15:55,150
And also because I never did
anything good in my life.

232
00:15:55,151 --> 00:15:57,100
So, knowing that I saved someone,
at least once...

233
00:15:57,101 --> 00:15:58,600
That could help me.

234
00:15:58,601 --> 00:16:00,550
If you could do that for me,
I would appreciate it.

235
00:16:01,800 --> 00:16:02,750
I'll see what I can do.

236
00:16:03,250 --> 00:16:04,350
Thank you.

237
00:16:04,351 --> 00:16:05,351
Don't mention it...

238
00:16:08,350 --> 00:16:09,200
Bye.

239
00:16:10,800 --> 00:16:12,650
Good bye...

240
00:16:18,700 --> 00:16:20,250
Why don't you dedicate your life to a cause?

241
00:16:20,251 --> 00:16:21,251
What cause?

242
00:16:21,252 --> 00:16:24,650
I don't know... Orphans in India?
Kids with aids in Africa?

243
00:16:24,651 --> 00:16:26,200
Why go so far?

244
00:16:26,201 --> 00:16:28,380
You're right.

245
00:16:28,381 --> 00:16:30,250
Poverty is everywhere.

246
00:16:31,400 --> 00:16:34,000
Why not help people in need,
here in Paris?

247
00:16:34,001 --> 00:16:35,450
People you could be a relief to.

248
00:16:35,451 --> 00:16:36,551
People like you?

249
00:16:36,552 --> 00:16:39,000
Yes.
Uh... no!

250
00:16:39,001 --> 00:16:40,001
I'm fine.

251
00:16:40,002 --> 00:16:41,302
Yeah...
You are SO fine.

252
00:16:41,303 --> 00:16:44,500
You merely tried jumping off a bridge.
Five minutes ago.

253
00:16:48,500 --> 00:16:51,950
If I gave you my life
would you know what to do with it?

254
00:16:56,700 --> 00:16:59,300
Give a carrot to a donkey,
you'll see if he knows what to do with it.

255
00:16:59,301 --> 00:17:03,450
Of course.
Of course I'd know what to do with it.

256
00:17:03,451 --> 00:17:08,400
Okay. Agreed.
I am yours.

257
00:17:10,700 --> 00:17:11,800
You gotta be kidding!

258
00:17:11,801 --> 00:17:14,350
Not at all.
What you said makes a lot of sense.

259
00:17:14,351 --> 00:17:17,450
You're right :
you are a good cause.

260
00:17:17,451 --> 00:17:19,900
I am yours.

261
00:17:19,901 --> 00:17:21,199
You're making fun of me.

262
00:17:21,200 --> 00:17:24,960
Not at all.
Can we start by buying some smokes?

263
00:17:26,300 --> 00:17:28,550
You mean you're going to stay next to me?

264
00:17:28,551 --> 00:17:32,100
Yeah. I will do whatever you ask.
Without arguing.

265
00:17:33,600 --> 00:17:35,350
You really are making fun of me.

266
00:17:35,351 --> 00:17:37,500
No.
Try me.

267
00:17:37,501 --> 00:17:38,501
Kiss me.

268
00:17:48,000 --> 00:17:49,000
Again?

269
00:17:49,001 --> 00:17:52,700
No, that's good enough.
I believe you.

270
00:17:52,701 --> 00:17:55,000
So, are we going to get smokes?

271
00:17:57,200 --> 00:17:59,000
