Now, give me your panties.

274
00:18:19,500 --> 00:18:22,450
Come one... don't be shy.
I have just dried mine.

275
00:18:22,451 --> 00:18:25,500
I can tell you, it feels better now.
Much warmer.

276
00:18:24,501 --> 00:18:26,800
I just told you : I'm fine.

277
00:18:26,801 --> 00:18:27,801
Okay.

278
00:18:31,500 --> 00:18:33,550
You know... it's the ladie's room here.

279
00:18:33,551 --> 00:18:34,551
Yeah?

280
00:18:34,552 --> 00:18:37,100
Yes, so can you tell this man
to go wash somewhere else?

281
00:18:37,101 --> 00:18:38,101
Who?

282
00:18:38,102 --> 00:18:40,650
Here! The man in that stall.
To whom you have handed a pair or pants.

283
00:18:40,651 --> 00:18:44,750
Don't judge a book by its cover : it's a woman.

284
00:18:45,450 --> 00:18:47,050
Yeah? With that kind of voice?

285
00:18:47,051 --> 00:18:51,200
It's a women on the inside.
The outside doesn't matter.

286
00:18:54,500 --> 00:18:55,700
What's going on?

287
00:18:55,701 --> 00:18:57,800
Nothing, just chatting between women.

288
00:18:57,801 --> 00:18:59,750
So? What are we doing now?

289
00:19:00,400 --> 00:19:02,850
Now, back to the business!

290
00:19:02,851 --> 00:19:05,000
Good!
Can we get some food on the way?

291
00:19:05,001 --> 00:19:07,100
I could die for some breakfast.

292
00:19:07,101 --> 00:19:10,500
Avoid mentioning 'dying'.
Lately, I...

293
00:19:10,501 --> 00:19:11,299
Okay.

294
00:19:11,300 --> 00:19:13,002
Thank you.

295
00:19:22,950 --> 00:19:25,600
I'm sorry... Can you move away from me?
I'm not used to that.

296
00:19:25,601 --> 00:19:26,401
Okay.

297
00:19:26,402 --> 00:19:28,700
And can you stop replying 'okay',
whenever I ask you something?

298
00:19:28,701 --> 00:19:29,701
Okay.

299
00:19:38,750 --> 00:19:40,250
You want a half?

300
00:19:40,251 --> 00:19:41,500
No, thanks.
I'm not hungry.

301
00:19:41,501 --> 00:19:44,500
Eat. You need strength,
if you want to leave.

302
00:19:44,501 --> 00:19:46,700
Look, this one is going to the South!

303
00:19:46,701 --> 00:19:48,500
I love the South!

304
00:19:48,501 --> 00:19:50,050
Me too.

305
00:19:50,051 --> 00:19:52,200
Really. At one point I was dreaming of living over there.
But I...

306
00:19:52,201 --> 00:19:53,201
Why didn't you move?

307
00:19:54,400 --> 00:19:55,400
Someday, maybe.

308
00:19:55,401 --> 00:19:56,700
Why not today?

309
00:19:58,400 --> 00:19:59,600
No. Today is not a good idea.

310
00:19:59,601 --> 00:20:02,500
It is! Let's take the train right now.
And go to the beach.

311
00:20:02,501 --> 00:20:03,501
Together.

312
00:20:07,650 --> 00:20:08,650
You know that song?

313
00:20:08,651 --> 00:20:09,651
Entirely.

314
00:20:09,652 --> 00:20:10,652
So? Are we going?

315
00:20:10,653 --> 00:20:11,300
Where?

316
00:20:11,301 --> 00:20:12,654
To the South!

317
00:20:12,355 --> 00:20:16,450
But... we can't go to the South
simply because you want to.

318
00:20:17,050 --> 00:20:18,450
Anyway, I have some issues to take care of.

319
00:20:18,451 --> 00:20:20,550
Issues?
Can I help you?

320
00:20:23,550 --> 00:20:24,400
Yeah... maybe.

321
00:20:24,401 --> 00:20:26,250
Awesome! What should I do?

322
00:20:26,750 --> 00:20:28,900
Nothing.
Just stay next to me.

323
00:20:28,901 --> 00:20:29,901
That will be enough?

324
00:20:29,902 --> 00:20:32,755
Yeah.
That way they're going to believe that...

325
00:20:34,300 --> 00:20:37,700
That we...
That we're together.

326
00:20:37,701 --> 00:20:39,050
And that's going to impress them.

327
00:20:39,500 --> 00:20:42,800
They are going to start respecting me.
See what I mean?

328
00:20:42,801 --> 00:20:43,801
Not at all.

329
00:20:43,802 --> 00:20:45,100
That's normal.

330
00:20:47,350 --> 00:20:49,850
First, Monsieur Frank, I thank you for seeing us.
I know you have better things to do...

331
00:20:49,851 --> 00:20:50,501
Cut the crap!

332
00:20:50,502 --> 00:20:51,502
Right.

333
00:20:51,503 --> 00:20:54,300
Listen. I know I owe you money.

334
00:20:54,301 --> 00:20:57,100
For you, it's not much.
But for me, it's an extraordinary amount.

335
00:20:57,101 --> 00:21:00,000
I am waiting for some cash sometime soon,
from my Argentina businesses, but...

336
00:21:00,001 --> 00:21:01,001
What kind of businesses?

337
00:21:01,002 --> 00:21:03,200
Uh... olive oil.

338
00:21:03,201 --> 00:21:04,400
Olive oil?

339
00:21:04,401 --> 00:21:06,500
It's winter over there.
No olive oil before five months.

340
00:21:06,501 --> 00:21:07,900
That's what you call 'sometime soon' ?

341
00:21:07,901 --> 00:21:10,500
True.
But I'm relying on stocks from... this month.

342
00:21:10,501 --> 00:21:12,350
But everything was stolen.

343
00:21:12,351 --> 00:21:15,450
People are starving so badly, over there.

344
00:21:15,451 --> 00:21:17,850
On the other hand, stealing olive oil...
it's ridiculous.

345
00:21:22,550 --> 00:21:23,550
Who's that girl?

346
00:21:23,551 --> 00:21:24,551
Who?

347
00:21:26,850 --> 00:21:27,900
Her?

348
00:21:27,901 --> 00:21:30,850
She's my associate.
Speaking of which, Frankie, I got to tell you...

349
00:21:30,851 --> 00:21:31,499
Frankie?

350
00:21:31,500 --> 00:21:32,110
Sorry.

351
00:21:32,111 --> 00:21:33,579
Watch it...

352
00:21:33,580 --> 00:21:36,854
I was thinking : you can't pay Frank back.
No need to hide it. You can't...

353
00:21:36,855 --> 00:21:41,550
At least, offer him a share of the pie.
I swear, Frank. It's a golden opportunity.

354
00:21:41,551 --> 00:21:44,150
Whatever you're offering,
I'm not interested.

355
00:21:47,100 --> 00:21:48,650
Why?
We used to have good deals.

356
00:21:48,651 --> 00:21:50,500
You're a loser, Andre.
Whatever you try, fails.

357
00:21:50,501 --> 00:21:53,400
The few times when you made money
that was just luck.

358
00:21:53,401 --> 00:21:55,750
It's a wonder you managed to stay in one piece.

359
00:21:55,751 --> 00:21:57,100
Look at yourself.

360
00:21:57,101 --> 00:21:58,900
You look like a bum.
You stink.

361
00:21:58,901 --> 00:22:01,450
People wouldn't even give you a penny.

362
00:22:01,451 --> 00:22:04,100
I'm sorry, Frank.
I didn't have the time to shave.

363
00:22:04,101 --> 00:22:07,000
Yesterday, I spent my time struggling to find a solution.

364
00:22:07,001 --> 00:22:08,500
I swear, when you hit rock bottom...

365
00:22:08,501 --> 00:22:09,751
Cut the theatrics, Andre!

366
00:22:09,752 --> 00:22:11,950
It's your fault, if you're in that situation.

367
00:22:16,800 --> 00:22:19,300
Well, then. I'm giving you six more hours
to find my 30 grands.

368
00:22:19,301 --> 00:22:21,650
If you fail, I'm sending two Yugos on your ass.
Is that clear?

369
00:22:21,651 --> 00:22:23,250
Two Yugos?

370
00:22:23,850 --> 00:22:25,050
Or two Bosnians, if you want.

371
00:22:29,050 --> 00:22:31,150
I only have one condition...

372
00:22:35,250 --> 00:22:38,730
Don't you have a little job?
Even a shitty one. I can take it...

373
00:22:38,731 --> 00:22:40,990
I think I know what he wants.

374
00:22:45,150 --> 00:22:46,500
Got a second, Monsieur Frank?

375
00:22:48,450 --> 00:22:50,650
You were supposed to shut up during this meeting.
Are you trying to screw things up, or what?

376
00:22:50,651 --> 00:22:53,950
As if you needed me to screw up.
You're negotiating like a white chick.

377
00:22:53,951 --> 00:22:55,100
Like a white chick?

378
00:22:55,900 --> 00:22:58,600
Why don't you give him what he wants?
Don't beat around the bush.

379
00:22:58,601 --> 00:22:59,601
Around the bush?

380
00:22:59,602 --> 00:23:00,602
Uh uh.

381
00:23:00,603 --> 00:23:03,800
Listen, Angela. You shut up for a minute.
Let me sort this business out. I'm back in a sec.

382
00:23:03,801 --> 00:23:04,800
What a 'business'...

383
00:23:04,801 --> 00:23:06,900
Damn... shut up!
You shut up.

384
00:23:13,700 --> 00:23:14,700
We were saying?

385
00:23:15,600 --> 00:23:16,600
Monsieur Frank!

386
00:23:19,100 --> 00:23:20,100
Monsieur Frank!

387
00:23:23,700 --> 00:23:26,450
Why don't you let your girlfriend talk?
She seems smarter than you.

388
00:23:26,625 --> 00:23:28,400
Well, then... no problem.

389
00:23:28,401 --> 00:23:31,500
If you want to chat with her.
Since we're associates...

390
00:23:31,501 --> 00:23:32,950
If you're talking to me,
it's as if you were talking to her.

391
00:23:32,951 --> 00:23:35,650
There's no...
Angela, will you please discuss with my friend?

392
00:23:35,651 --> 00:23:37,750
Where do you want to do it?

393
00:23:38,450 --> 00:23:40,800
I've got a small lounge, right upstairs.
We won't be disturbed.

394
00:23:40,801 --> 00:23:41,801
Fine.

395
00:23:50,150 --> 00:23:52,300
You're unbelievable, you...

396
00:23:58,850 --> 00:24:01,500
Angela! Angela...
That guy is a killer. He's gonna mess with your head.

397
00:24:01,501 --> 00:24:03,500
Shhhh...
Let me handle this.

398
00:24:03,501 --> 00:24:06,250
I'm going to make him
an offer he can't refuse.

399
00:24:07,000 --> 00:24:08,300
Be nice.

400
00:24:20,300 --> 00:24:21,650
Where have you been?
I've been waiting for an hour!

401
00:24:21,651 --> 00:24:24,250
It didn't take an hour. I stayed for five minutes.
It all went very well.

402
00:24:24,251 --> 00:24:27,300
You don't realize, poor girl.
That guy is a killer!

403
00:24:27,301 --> 00:24:29,300
He could as well have killed you.

404
00:24:29,301 --> 00:24:33,250
I guess I got lucky, then.
Here... It's for you.

405
00:24:33,251 --> 00:24:34,251
What is that?

406
00:24:34,252 --> 00:24:36,000
Paper.
With pictures on it.

407
00:24:36,050 --> 00:24:37,500
It is called 'money'.

408
00:24:39,350 --> 00:24:40,350
And my debts?

409
00:24:40,351 --> 00:24:43,450
You don't owe him anything anymore.
He wiped your slate clean.

410
00:24:43,451 --> 00:24:45,680
You're white as snow, now.
You can breathe.

411
00:24:45,681 --> 00:24:48,500
And take the time you need
to feel better again.

412
00:24:48,501 --> 00:24:50,800
Angela. What have you done?
Did you sell your mother, or what?

413
00:24:50,801 --> 00:24:51,450
Of course not.

414
00:24:51,451 --> 00:24:52,882
Wait. Tell me.

415
00:24:52,883 --> 00:24:55,320
Ah. Why do you care?
You had a problem...

416
00:24:55,321 --> 00:24:56,680
and it's solved.
Now, look ahead of you.

417
00:24:56,681 --> 00:24:59,050
Move forwards, now.

418
00:24:59,051 --> 00:25:02,500
Wait. I'm not moving anywhere.
I don't want any dirty money.

419
00:25:02,501 --> 00:25:04,100
What do you mean by 'dirty money' ?

420
00:25:03,502 --> 00:25:06,300
If you did nasty stuff...
then I don't want it.

421
00:25:06,301 --> 00:25:10,350
When you take money from an ATM
do you wonder where it comes from?

422
00:25:10,351 --> 00:25:12,650
It's coming from the machine.
And I'm fine with that.

423
00:25:12,651 --> 00:25:14,700
Well... today I am the ATM.

424
00:25:14,701 --> 00:25:17,900
BEEP Take your money.
And stop bitching about it.

425
00:25:20,600 --> 00:25:22,200
Actually, it helps me a lot.

426
00:25:23,100 --> 00:25:24,450
How much is there?

427
00:25:24,451 --> 00:25:26,500
Enough to repay the Spaniard.

428
00:25:26,700 --> 00:25:28,450
That's so great!

429
00:25:31,325 --> 00:25:33,100
How do you know I owe
money to the Spaniard?

430
00:25:33,700 --> 00:25:36,050
Everybody knows about your debts,
my poor Andre...

431
00:25:36,051 --> 00:25:37,051
I don't want it anymore!

432
00:25:37,052 --> 00:25:38,052
Why don't you?

433
00:25:38,053 --> 00:25:40,650
Because I'm convinced you've done
nasty things with Frank.

434
00:25:40,651 --> 00:25:42,300
I'm not a pimp.
You hear me?

435
00:25:42,301 --> 00:25:43,100
Nonsense!

436
00:25:43,101 --> 00:25:45,000
Yes, sense!
Give me that...

437
00:25:46,300 --> 00:25:48,500
Wait... Do you think I didn't see you
dancing in front of him?

438
00:25:48,501 --> 00:25:49,501
Dancing, me?

439
00:25:49,502 --> 00:25:51,300
You kept showing him your panties.
I saw it!

440
00:25:51,301 --> 00:25:52,301
You have eyes behind your back?

441
00:25:52,302 --> 00:25:55,300
I noticed he wasn't focused on
what I was saying.

442
00:25:55,301 --> 00:25:58,000
What you were saying
wasn't really interesting...

443
00:25:58,001 --> 00:25:59,400
I was talking business, okay?

444
00:25:59,401 --> 00:26:02,450
Business has its code, its own language.
It's mostly body language.

445
00:26:02,451 --> 00:26:05,200
You got to look weak one moment,
so as to catch your prey unaware!

446
00:26:05,201 --> 00:26:06,900
But you're not fishing trout, Andre.

447
00:26:06,901 --> 00:26:10,000
You're dealing with a crook.
Behaving like a grade school student...

448
00:26:10,001 --> 00:26:12,450
At least I have some pride left.
A few principles.

449
00:26:12,451 --> 00:26:13,451
Probably too much for you.

450
00:26:13,452 --> 00:26:15,850
Then why didn't use your principles?

451
00:26:15,851 --> 00:26:17,500
Frank was like a marshmallow, today.

452
00:26:17,501 --> 00:26:19,550
You could have asked for 10 grands. Easy...

453
00:26:19,551 --> 00:26:20,551
Never.

454
00:26:21,350 --> 00:26:22,350
I considered it.

455
00:26:22,351 --> 00:26:25,800
You know... brains are large.
You can use more than this tiny piece.

456
00:26:25,801 --> 00:26:28,450
You are so wrong, poor girl.
I'm using all of it. All!

457
00:26:28,451 --> 00:26:30,500
I think all the time.

458
00:26:30,501 --> 00:26:32,550
Right now, I'm thinking
you should leave me alone.

459
00:26:32,551 --> 00:26:34,600
But you're thinking small.
Paying small debts.

460
00:26:34,601 --> 00:26:37,100
Buying a small plane ticket.
To quickly go to New York...

461
00:26:37,101 --> 00:26:39,150
So as to sell your Brooklyn apartment.

462
00:26:42,930 --> 00:26:44,550
How come you know about my Brooklyn penthouse?

463
00:26:44,551 --> 00:26:46,400
You call this hole a penthouse?

464
00:26:46,401 --> 00:26:48,850
It was cheap when I bought it,
but since then the price must have increased...

465
00:26:48,851 --> 00:26:50,980
Who cares about your Brooklyn apartment?

466
00:26:50,981 --> 00:26:54,450
It's not the problem. Your problem is
that all you want is to run away.

467
00:26:54,451 --> 00:26:56,600
All the time...
Instead of taking a break.

468
00:26:56,601 --> 00:26:58,850
Instead of breathing.

469
00:26:59,540 --> 00:27:03,000
Letting oxygen climb up to your brain.
Making it happy.

470
00:27:03,001 --> 00:27:05,650
So that it helps you take the right decisions.

471
00:27:05,651 --> 00:27:07,850
Now, breathe!

472
00:27:08,500 --> 00:27:09,450
Breathe...

473
00:27:10,250 --> 00:27:11,200
Breathe!

474
00:27:12,200 --> 00:27:14,000
Good... Look.
Come here.

475
00:27:16,500 --> 00:27:17,500
Lift up your head.

476
00:27:17,501 --> 00:27:18,501
Breathe.

477
00:27:20,450 --> 00:27:21,450
Breathe.

478
00:27:21,451 --> 00:27:22,451
There... look.

479
00:27:22,452 --> 00:27:23,452
Breathe!

480
00:27:23,453 --> 00:27:26,500
Look.
There...

481
00:27:27,300 --> 00:27:28,300
The clouds...

482
00:27:29,850 --> 00:27:30,850
The birds...

483
00:27:31,550 --> 00:27:33,200
The city...

484
00:27:33,650 --> 00:27:35,150
All around us.

485
00:27:36,350 --> 00:27:37,350
Breathe.

486
00:27:41,480 --> 00:27:44,950
Is it not the most beautiful
city in the world?

487
00:27:46,350 --> 00:27:49,300
So, how should I have handled Frank?

488
00:27:51,100 --> 00:27:53,650
By telling him the truth.
That's all.

489
00:27:54,600 --> 00:27:56,450
What truth?

490
00:27:57,300 --> 00:27:59,500
The only one you don't want to hear.

491
00:28:01,700 --> 00:28:04,150
The money I owe you is dirty.
Coming mostly from sex and drugs.

492
00:28:04,151 --> 00:28:07,050
I'll never return it
because I don't want to be part of that shit.

493
00:28:07,051 --> 00:28:11,150
Anyway, I'll never see your ugly face again.
I won't lose any more time with scum like you.

494
00:28:11,350 --> 00:28:12,350
Bravo, Andre!

495
00:28:13,800 --> 00:28:15,300
You really think I should have said that?

496
00:28:15,301 --> 00:28:16,800
Isn't that what you were thinking?

497
00:28:16,801 --> 00:28:18,700
We can't always say what we think, Angela.

498
00:28:18,701 --> 00:28:20,600
Why not?
Maybe life would be better that way.

499
00:28:20,601 --> 00:28:23,000
