who take a second serving of bread to finish their cheese.

1021
00:54:08,051 --> 00:54:10,250
And then they take more cheese,
to finish the bread.

1022
00:54:10,251 --> 00:54:13,445
And if with the French, it's even more complicated.
They take more wine, to finish both.

1023
00:54:13,446 --> 00:54:16,150
Afterwards, they're suprised to still be
around lunch at three in the afternoon.

1024
00:54:16,151 --> 00:54:17,625
What kind of lame example was that?

1025
00:54:17,626 --> 00:54:19,850
I don't like cheese.
And I don't see your point anyway.

1026
00:54:19,851 --> 00:54:21,860
I'm in trouble.
And I'm trying to get out of it like I can.

1027
00:54:21,861 --> 00:54:23,690
But there no way for you to understand that.

1028
00:54:23,691 --> 00:54:25,960
You can jump from a bridge, fuck whoever,
smoke like a drunkard...

1029
00:54:25,961 --> 00:54:26,961
Nothing is a problem to you.

1030
00:54:27,550 --> 00:54:29,740
Belittling my credit won't make yours any greater.

1031
00:54:31,300 --> 00:54:32,700
You really are an annoyance, Angela.

1032
00:54:32,701 --> 00:54:34,780
Why do you always have
to intellectualize everything?

1033
00:54:34,781 --> 00:54:36,350
She keeps doing that.
It's irritating.

1034
00:54:36,600 --> 00:54:39,325
I'm just trying to show you the mechanism
that causes you to always screw up.

1035
00:54:39,326 --> 00:54:41,560
She's got a point :
you're screwed.

1036
00:54:45,300 --> 00:54:47,750
Listen, buddy.
You're going to let me handle this, okay?

1037
00:54:47,751 --> 00:54:48,751
I'll be right back.

1038
00:54:49,630 --> 00:54:51,060
Damn, Angela...
Why are you doing this to me?

1039
00:54:51,061 --> 00:54:52,950
You said you're here to help me.
Why are you depressing me?

1040
00:54:52,951 --> 00:54:54,200
Ah? You were feeling better before?

1041
00:54:54,201 --> 00:54:57,300
Yeah! Yeah... Nothing exceptionnal,
but I sure was far less confused.

1042
00:54:57,301 --> 00:54:59,000
Why did you want to jump from a bridge, then?

1043
00:54:59,001 --> 00:55:00,001
Because...

1044
00:55:00,970 --> 00:55:02,825
See?
She's definitely messing with me.

1045
00:55:02,826 --> 00:55:05,225
What was the initial agreement?
Don't you remember our agreement?

1046
00:55:05,226 --> 00:55:07,355
You were supposed to shut up and follow me.
Remember?

1047
00:55:07,356 --> 00:55:08,500
Yes.
You're right

1048
00:55:08,501 --> 00:55:09,780
Well, here you go.

1049
00:55:10,760 --> 00:55:11,850
Shut up, then.

1050
00:55:11,851 --> 00:55:13,480
Don't say anything, okay?

1051
00:55:13,481 --> 00:55:13,979
Okay.

1052
00:55:13,980 --> 00:55:14,929
No!

1053
00:55:14,930 --> 00:55:16,700
Don't even say 'okay'.

1054
00:55:17,320 --> 00:55:19,250
You shut 100% up.
Okay?

1055
00:55:20,150 --> 00:55:21,880
Do you understand '100%' ?

1056
00:55:22,960 --> 00:55:26,000
Are you done?
Can we start doing serious business, now?

1057
00:55:26,650 --> 00:55:29,000
Angela.
Can you play 'Simon says' ?

1058
00:55:29,001 --> 00:55:30,001
I love it!

1059
00:55:30,002 --> 00:55:31,650
Simon says :
Beat the shit out of these three assholes.

1060
00:55:31,651 --> 00:55:32,651
Okay!

1061
00:55:39,740 --> 00:55:40,750
I'm glad I'm rid of them.

1062
00:55:40,751 --> 00:55:42,600
So?
What are we doing now?

1063
00:55:42,601 --> 00:55:43,601
Shhhh!

1064
00:55:44,200 --> 00:55:45,600
We don't say anything.

1065
00:55:47,170 --> 00:55:48,700
Now, we're going to go...

1066
00:55:50,745 --> 00:55:52,100
... going to go that way.

1067
00:55:55,000 --> 00:55:57,480
Angela...
I'd like to know more about you, actually.

1068
00:55:58,000 --> 00:56:00,130
Your past.
Back when you were on Earth.

1069
00:56:00,131 --> 00:56:00,860
Yeah?

1070
00:56:00,861 --> 00:56:02,132
Yes.

1071
00:56:02,650 --> 00:56:05,270
Really. I want to know you better.
How were you, as a kid?

1072
00:56:08,215 --> 00:56:11,300
We were living in Paris.
In the 13rd district.

1073
00:56:11,301 --> 00:56:13,650
I'm the eldest of eight children.

1074
00:56:13,651 --> 00:56:15,480
I'm the one who took care of them.

1075
00:56:18,675 --> 00:56:20,200
My mother ran away when I was 15.

1076
00:56:20,201 --> 00:56:22,500
And my father was drunk all day.

1077
00:56:23,350 --> 00:56:25,350
I would take the little ones to school.

1078
00:56:25,351 --> 00:56:28,550
Then I would work as a prostitute,
so as to pay for their food.

1079
00:56:28,551 --> 00:56:32,100
I died of an ovarian tumor when I was 23.

1080
00:56:32,500 --> 00:56:34,500
Damn... poor thing.
It's horrible.

1081
00:56:37,290 --> 00:56:41,600
What kind of life was that ?
Whoa...

1082
00:56:42,025 --> 00:56:45,050
And I thought I was in trouble...
I should stop complaining.

1083
00:56:46,300 --> 00:56:47,200
Why are you smiling?

1084
00:56:47,250 --> 00:56:49,500
Because you're so gullible...
You believed that.

1085
00:56:49,501 --> 00:56:50,501
Ah?
That wasn't true?

1086
00:56:51,000 --> 00:56:51,600
Nah...

1087
00:56:51,970 --> 00:56:54,740
No.
I'm a rich girl from New Jersey.

1088
00:56:55,185 --> 00:56:56,600
Daddy used to work for the U.N.

1089
00:56:56,601 --> 00:56:58,400
And mummy was working
to bring people together...

1090
00:56:58,401 --> 00:57:01,800
... by being humped by all the males
she could find at cocktail parties.

1091
00:57:01,801 --> 00:57:04,300
On my 16th birthday,
I got my first Ferrari.

1092
00:57:04,301 --> 00:57:06,800
And I smashed it in the first fall I met.

1093
00:57:06,801 --> 00:57:08,450
Just so that my father would notice me...

1094
00:57:08,451 --> 00:57:10,000
... at least at my funeral.

1095
00:57:10,001 --> 00:57:12,000
I'm lost, now...
Which was your life?

1096
00:57:12,001 --> 00:57:14,450
Which one makes your own easier to endure?

1097
00:57:17,250 --> 00:57:18,000
I don't know.

1098
00:57:18,001 --> 00:57:22,400
I can make up a thousand of lives.
But yours will still be the same.

1099
00:57:22,401 --> 00:57:24,400
You'll have to accept it.

1100
00:57:25,580 --> 00:57:28,430
I...
I see what you mean, Angela.

1101
00:57:28,431 --> 00:57:31,185
And...
I'm working on it.

1102
00:57:33,280 --> 00:57:35,640
But still...
I want to know you.

1103
00:57:36,180 --> 00:57:39,170
Who were you?
Before...

1104
00:57:50,575 --> 00:57:52,125
I don't know who I am.

1105
00:57:52,126 --> 00:57:54,000
How can't you know?

1106
00:57:54,001 --> 00:57:56,200
You come from the sky.
You're in the best position to know...

1107
00:57:56,201 --> 00:57:59,000
We can't access our past.
It's top secret data.

1108
00:57:59,350 --> 00:58:00,250
Really?

1109
00:58:01,750 --> 00:58:02,980
That gotta suck.

1110
00:58:06,720 --> 00:58:07,480
Are my questions bothering you?

1111
00:58:07,481 --> 00:58:08,481
No.

1112
00:58:08,482 --> 00:58:11,800
You're interested in me.
That means you're getting interested in you.

1113
00:58:12,000 --> 00:58:13,150
I'm not really interesting.

1114
00:58:13,151 --> 00:58:14,151
Of course you are!

1115
00:58:14,930 --> 00:58:16,220
You're good looking, smart...

1116
00:58:16,221 --> 00:58:17,430
Stop making fun of me.

1117
00:58:17,431 --> 00:58:19,000
You are!
I tell you!

1118
00:58:19,001 --> 00:58:21,950
It's all inside. But you don't see it.
You can't pull it out.

1119
00:58:21,951 --> 00:58:24,000
I'm trying.
I know...

1120
00:58:25,550 --> 00:58:26,380
But it's not easy.

1121
00:58:26,381 --> 00:58:28,750
Yes it's easy!
Come, I'll show you!

1122
00:58:31,100 --> 00:58:33,790
Look in the mirror!
What do you see?

1123
00:58:34,460 --> 00:58:37,000
Look in the mirror...
What do you see?

1124
00:58:38,660 --> 00:58:39,660
I see...

1125
00:58:41,020 --> 00:58:42,020
A wonderful girl.

1126
00:58:42,021 --> 00:58:45,600
